# API design guidelines

The canonical rule content lives in [`coding-rules/rules/api-design.md`](mdc:coding-rules/rules/api-design.md) — a single source of truth shared with Claude Code so the tools cannot drift.

These rules apply only when designing or implementing HTTP (REST) APIs; skip them for code with no API surface. When they do apply, read and follow `coding-rules/rules/api-design.md`: published contracts evolve additively, URL-path versioning only as a last resort and only by human decision, one RFC 9457-style error envelope with stable machine-mappable codes, pagination from day one, idempotency for consequential POSTs, and schema-driven boundary validation with OpenAPI generated from the same source of truth.
